18/12/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Meeting in Belgrade Friday (16 December), the police chiefs of Southeast European countries agreed to enhance regional co-operation. They were attending the annual Executive Board Meeting of the Southeast European Police Chiefs Association (SEPCA), co-organised by the OSCE Mission to Serbia-Montenegro and the Serbian Interior Ministry. Addressing the participants, the head of the OSCE Mission's Law Enforcement Department, Nils Bechmann, called for concrete programmes to enable SEPCA to become a strong and viable structure. (OSCE Web site - 16/12/05)
